Preamble

This license establishes the terms under which a "Package" may be copied,
modified, distributed, and/or redistributed. The intent is that the
Copyright Holder maintains some artistic or stylistic control over the
development of the Package, while giving the recipients of the Package
sufficient rights to use and distribute the Package in a reasonably
convenient manner.

Definitions

"Copyright Holder" means the author(s) of the base Package, and any
other entity that may hold copyright in the Package.

"Modified Package" means a Package that has been edited, modified, or
augmented by someone other than the Copyright Holder.

"You" and "your" means the person who would like to copy, distribute,
or modify the Package.

"Package" means the collection of files distributed by the Copyright Holder,
including documentation, source code, data, files in standard archival
formats (e.g., .tar.gz, .zip, etc.), and any supporting scripts,
applications, or documentation.

"Standard Version" refers to such a Package if it has not been modified,
or has been modified in accordance with the wishes of the Copyright Holder.

"Modified Version" refers to the Package, if any, that is being distributed
and/or modified by you.

"Standardized Resource" means any file, directory, or other resource
that is distributed with the Package, including any modifications that
you make.

